defs.name: Bound
defs.docs:
Bound is used to defines the two ends of a range, more explicit than Option<u8>
 None means that we don't limit that side of the range at all.
 Include means we use the given bytes as a limit and *include* anything at that exact key
 Exclude means we use the given bytes as a limit and *exclude* anything at that exact key

defs.name: Selected
defs.docs:
Only writes for linked blocks - does a few more reads to save some writes.
 Probably uses more gas, but less total disk usage.

attributes.value: / Only writes for linked blocks - does a few more reads to save some writes.
/ Probably uses more gas, but less total disk usage.
/ Note that you need a trusted source (eg. own contract) to set/remove checkpoints.
/ Useful when the checkpoint setting happens in the same contract as the snapshotting.
